          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Trump’s plan gets support</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/trump-remarks-opposition-ceasefire-talks-hamas-israel.png" alt="Donald Trump's remarks drew swift opposition and were certain to roil the ceasefire talks between Hamas and Israel" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">Donald Trump's remarks drew swift opposition and were certain to roil the ceasefire talks between Hamas and Israel. Credits: AP Photo</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Israel's PM Benjamin Netanyahu has backed a US proposal for Gaza’s future, which <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-02-2025-h2-2-involves-displacing-its-palestinian-residents?source=website" target="_blank">involves displacing its Palestinian residents</a> and preventing both Hamas and the Palestinian Authority from governing the enclave. The plan, pushed by Secretary of State Marco Rubio, has been widely criticized by Arab nations and human rights groups as a violation of international law amounting to ethnic cleansing.</p>

          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Israel’s Defense Minister, Israel Katz, announced a directorate to facilitate the “voluntary departure” of Palestinians from Gaza, offering assistance for relocation to third countries. Meanwhile, Saudi Arabia is leading efforts to counter Trump’s plan, proposing a Gulf-led reconstruction initiative. The Saudi Foreign Ministry said it rejects any attempts to displace Palestinians. Egypt is also putting forth reconstruction plans for Gaza.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Netanyahu is facing pressure from both the US and Israeli hostage families to move forward with the Gaza ceasefire’s second phase, which is being negotiated. 33 captives are expected to be released during this stage. However, his fellow far-right coalition members threaten to withdraw support if the war ends. </p>
        </mj-text>
