            <strong>🇺🇸 Rubio met Lavrov and agreed to consider mutual interests</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">US and Russia counterparts Sergey Lavrov and Marco Rubio held 4.5 hours of talks in Riyadh. The <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-19-02-2025-br1-4-thediscussion-focused-on-ukraine?source=website" target="_blank">discussions focused on Ukraine</a>, but Kyiv was excluded, leading to criticism from President Zelenskyy. Both sides agreed to form high-level teams to work toward a peace settlement, though a meeting between Trump and Putin is not imminent any time soon.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The US called the talks a positive step, while Russia said both sides acknowledged each other’s interests. They also agreed to improve diplomatic relations and discuss future economic cooperation. Shortly after the talks, air raid sirens went off in Kyiv due to a Russian missile threat. Meanwhile, Zelenskyy met Turkish President Erdogan and criticized negotiations happening without Ukraine’s involvement. He stated that Ukraine will not accept ultimatums and will continue to resist Russian aggression.</p>
        </mj-text>
